snippet.textDisplay:
Law wanting backdoors in the case of a crime:
Couldn't they build a giant giant server where data is only fed into it? All data that passes through the main servers is copied over and stored in the 'backup/security' server. This server can store all messages, etc but can only be accessed in real life in the server room with a special ID code that only the police have? This means they have all backups of data but is kept 100% private unless the police specifically need data on a single specific person in the case of some more extreme crime (we're talking rape, murder, terrorism that kind of level)
